GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 302
Short Title: The Sergeant Mickey Hutchens Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Hanig, Jones, and Hise (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 18, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW LAW ENFORCEMENT, PROBATION/PAROLE, AND
3 CORRECTIONAL OFFICERS WHO HOLD AN ADVANCED LAW ENFORCEMENT
4 OR CORRECTIONS CERTIFICATE ISSUED BY THE NORTH CAROLINA CRIMINAL
5 JUSTICE EDUCATION AND TRAINING STANDARDS COMMISSION OR THE
6 ADVANCED LAW ENFORCEMENT CERTIFICATE ISSUED BY THE NORTH
7 CAROLINA SHERIFFS' EDUCATION AND TRAINING STANDARDS COMMISSION
8 TO PURCHASE, AT FULL COST, UP TO FOUR YEARS' CREDITABLE SERVICE IN
9 THE TEACHERS' AND STATE EMPLOYEES' RETIREMENT SYSTEM OR THE
10 LOCAL GOVERNMENTAL EMPLOYEES' RETIREMENT SYSTEM.
11 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
12 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 135-4.5 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
13 "(h) Purchases of Service Credit for Advanced Law Enforcement or Advanced
14 Corrections Certificates. – Notwithstanding any other provision of this Article to the contrary, a
15 member in service with five or more years of membership service who has been awarded either
16 (i) the Advanced Law Enforcement Certificate issued by either the North Carolina Criminal
17 Justice Education and Training Standards Commission under the authority granted under Chapter
18 17C of the General Statutes or the North Carolina Sheriffs' Education and Training Standards
19 Commission under the authority granted under Chapter 17E of the General Statutes or (ii) the
20 Advanced Corrections Certificate issued by the North Carolina Criminal Justice Education and
21 Training Standards Commission under the authority granted under Chapter 17C of the General
22 Statutes may purchase creditable service subject to all of the following:
23 (1) The member may purchase up to a total of four years of creditable service
24 under this subsection.
25 (2) Service may only be purchased under this subsection upon or after receipt of
26 the applicable certificate.
27 (3) G.S. 135-4(b) does not apply to purchases under this subsection.
28 (4) Purchases of service under this subsection shall be made by paying a lump
29 sum amount to the Annuity Savings Fund. Purchases shall not be associated
30 with any specific compensation or period of time. The amount payable shall
31 be equal to the full liability increase of the Retirement System due to the
32 additional service credits purchased plus an administrative fee that is set by
33 the Board of Trustees. The full liability increase shall be calculated on the
34 basis of the same assumptions used for the purposes of the actuarial valuation
35 of the liabilities of the Retirement System, except for the following
36 assumptions specific to this calculation: (i) the allowance shall be assumed to
*S302-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 commence at the earliest age at which the member could retire on an
2 unreduced retirement allowance and (ii) there shall be assumed annual
3 postretirement allowance increases set by the Board of Trustees upon the
4 advice of the consulting actuary.
5 (5) An employer may pay all or part of the cost of a purchase of service under this
6 subsection. To the extent that the purchase is paid by the employer, the amount
7 paid by the employer shall be credited to the Pension Accumulation Fund. To
8 the extent that the purchase is paid by the member, the amount paid by the
9 member shall be credited to the member's accumulated contributions and
10 interest in the Annuity Savings Fund."
11 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 135-4(b) reads as rewritten:
12 "(b) In Unless specifically provided under G.S. 135-4.5, in no case shall more than one
13 year of service be creditable for all services in one year. Service rendered for the regular school
14 year in any district shall be equivalent to one year's service. Service rendered by a school
15 employee in a job-sharing position shall be credited at the rate of one-half year for each regular
16 school year of employment."
17 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 128-26.5 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
18 "(h) Purchases of Service Credit for Advanced Law Enforcement Certificate. –
19 Notwithstanding any other provision of this Article to the contrary, a member in service with five
20 or more years of membership service who has been awarded the Advanced Law Enforcement
21 Certificate issued by either the North Carolina Criminal Justice Education and Training
22 Standards Commission under the authority granted under Chapter 17C of the General Statutes or
23 the North Carolina Sheriffs' Education and Training Standards Commission under the authority
24 granted under Chapter 17E of the General Statutes may purchase creditable service subject to all
25 of the following:
26 (1) The member may purchase up to a total of four years of creditable service
27 under this subsection.
28 (2) Service may only be purchased under this subsection upon or after receipt of
29 the applicable certificate.
30 (3) G.S. 128-26(b) does not apply to purchases under this subsection.
31 (4) Purchases of service under this subsection shall be made by paying a lump
32 sum amount to the Annuity Savings Fund. Purchases shall not be associated
33 with any specific compensation or period of time. The amount payable shall
34 be equal to the full liability increase of the Retirement System due to the
35 additional service credits purchased plus an administrative fee that is set by
36 the Board of Trustees. The full liability increase shall be calculated on the
37 basis of the same assumptions used for the purposes of the actuarial valuation
38 of the liabilities of the Retirement System, except for the following
39 assumptions specific to this calculation: (i) the allowance shall be assumed to
40 commence at the earliest age at which the member could retire on an
41 unreduced retirement allowance and (ii) there shall be assumed annual
42 postretirement allowance increases set by the Board of Trustees upon the
43 advice of the consulting actuary.
44 (5) An employer may pay all or part of the cost of a purchase of service under this
45 subsection. To the extent that the purchase is paid by the employer, the amount
46 paid by the employer shall be credited to the Pension Accumulation Fund. To
47 the extent that the purchase is paid by the member, the amount paid by the
48 member shall be credited to the member's accumulated contributions and
49 interest in the Annuity Savings Fund."
50 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 128-26(b) reads as rewritten:
